help:
usage: generate/tls/certificate [-h] [-i] [-g] [-o OUTPUT] [-v] [-s SIZE]
                                [-e EXPIRE] [-a] [--country COUNTRY]
                                [--state STATE] [--locality LOCALITY]
                                [--organization ORGANIZATION]
                                [--organizational-unit ORGANIZATIONAL_UNIT]
                                [-n COMMON_NAME] [--email EMAIL]

    Generate an SSL/TLS X.509 certificate in PEM format (provide certificate authority as input).
    

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -i, --iterate         iterate over input
  -g, --generate        generate each output
  -o OUTPUT, --output OUTPUT
                        output to file
  -v, --verbose         print debug info
  -s SIZE, --size SIZE  key size (2048 bits)
  -e EXPIRE, --expire EXPIRE
                        expire time (365 days)
  -a, --authority       indicate certificate authority (False)
  --country COUNTRY     country name (AU)
  --state STATE         state (Some-State)
  --locality LOCALITY   locality (None)
  --organization ORGANIZATION
                        organization (Internet Widgets Pty Ltd)
  --organizational-unit ORGANIZATIONAL_UNIT
                        organizational unit (None)
  -n COMMON_NAME, --common-name COMMON_NAME
                        common name (None)
  --email EMAIL         email (None)

                          [--interface INTERFACE] [-m] [-c CA]

    Proxy HTTP traffic.
    

optional arguments:

  -g, --generate        generate each output
  -o OUTPUT, --output OUTPUT

  -p PORT, --port PORT  listen on port
  --interface INTERFACE

  -m, --mitm            mitm proxied traffic
  -c CA, --ca CA        mitm certificate authority (PEM key+cert)
